            <h3 data-uuid="0b05a6ba7a254de1ae68053644fb7271">Part 2: Write an Explanatory Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="b73d699730f241629d0453e0dc632a97">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="39b8f1d330ef40028b30fa71748e59e9">Slavery
                was controversial in America long before the United States came into existence.
                During the first half of the 19th century, a powerful movement developed to
                abolish slavery. Meanwhile, most southerners remained deeply committed to the
                practice. Yet on several occasions when a crisis developed over slavery,
                politicians from the North and the South found a way to compromise and hold the
                nation together.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="156225a4c5794a5a88d66997f1125bb0">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="888fac573481431c97d764615a0d770b">In
                the decade leading up to the Civil War, why were U.S. political leaders unable
                to reach a lasting compromise over the issue of slavery? Write an essay in
                response to this question.</p>
            <p data-uuid="d8fa00c06eaf4cd885fdbdb5fbbb985e">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="92e56de574454650901b00e9863b55d3">
                <li data-uuid="d11d19cc889646c1b5c39192e6d1e5c5">
                    Review your notes and sources before you start writing.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="a3e67a94135a477689d65be0c5b3f26a">
                    Use at least <i>three</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic
                    with relevant, well-chosen text evidence from the documents.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="06349fee829a413ab3074cda7fa1567d">
                    Cite specific text evidence from each of the sources in your
                    response.
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="78fc368effe0421f8a6e6b699204e1c2">
                    Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph.</li>
                <li data-uuid="cbf2dec3129946af8cb29beb60b31b2d">Organize your essay in a clear way that focuses on the topic and supports it with explanations and facts.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="733b77eefc264975ba5b4c8756f83a13">Write a conclusion that
                    sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.<br />
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
